    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 1: DAGL-α (DAGLA) antibody specificity validation using knockout mice.\n\nFigure 3: immunogold EM imaging of the ventromedial nucleus of the hypothalamus showed DAGL-α (DAGLA) particles at the membranes of dendrites and dendritic spines. 54.4 % of dendrites and 44.4 % of dendritic spines were DAGL-α immunopositive.\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: M&M:\n\"Six wild-type C57BL/6 N female mice (3-5 month old) were used in this study.\"\n\nantibody:\nDAGL-α (2 μg/ml, made in rabbit, Frontier Science co. Ltd, Shinko-nishi, Ishikari, Hokkaido, Japan)\n\n\"Specificity of the DAGL-α antibody was assessed in hypothalamus of DAGL-α knock-out mice processed for this method.\n...\nThe specificity of the DAGL-α antibody has also been confirmed in previous studies (Yoshida et al. 2006; Uchigashima et al. 2007; Puente et al. 2011).\"",
